
To install on a DHCP server, become root and run:
    mkdir -p /cdg/adhoc
    cd /cdg/adhoc
    tar xf adhoc-connect-x.y.z.tar
    ln -s adhoc-connect-x.y.z adhoc-connect
    cd adhoc-connect
    cp etc/adhoc-connect.cron /etc/cron.d
    
 To upgrade:
    cd /cdg/adhoc
    wget https://utveckling.its.chalmers.se/sites/utveckling.its.chalmers.se/files/adhoc-connect-v.w.u.tar
    rm adhoc-connect
    ln -s adhoc-connect-v.w.u adhoc-connect
    cp etc/adhoc-connect.cron /etc/cron.d (probably not necessary though)